<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>France head coach Didier Deschamps has hailed the transformation of Antony Martial who he says is now 'on the right track' on and off the pitch.</p>

<p>Martial enjoyed a fine campaign for Manchester United last season where he finished the club's top scorer on 23 goals.</p>

<p>He was also on form for France against Croatia in the Nations League on Tuesday night in his first start for his country since March 2018.</p>

<p>France's Anthony Martial celebrates after his shot led to a Croatia own goal on Tuesday night</p>

<p>France head coach Didier Deschamps praised Martial's transformation over the last 12 months</p>

<p>Martial set up Antoine Griezmann for France's first goal, saw his shot come off the post to be put in by Croatia's Dominik Livakovic for their second and played a key role in the world champions recording a 4-2 victory in Paris. </p>

<p>Deschamps singled Martial out for praise, adding that the United attacker's hard work over the last year had paid off.</p>

<p>Martial finished Manchester United's top scorer with 23 goals in all competitions last season</p>

<p>Deschamps said: 'I wouldn't say that he has undergone a metamorphosis but he has changed. I have noticed as well off of the pitch. He is capable of making a difference, very solid. He is on the right track.' </p>

<p>Martial, who will now return to United in preparation for the new Premier League season, told French television channel TF1: 'It's been a long time since I played for France and it was important to me to have a good match.' </p>
